This paper deals with the optimization of network management in 5G networks, which involves decision-making about activating or deactivating nodes, running network functions, and routing traffic. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves formulating an optimization problem, which suggests that it could also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. The paper also deals with information theory (cs.IT) and data centers (cs.DC), which are other possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper mentions the integration of an optimization module within the management and orchestration framework of 5G, which suggests that it could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
